parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to stick or lock, making it difficult or impossible to use, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belt will not come out of the retractor
the seat belt locks or sticks
the seat belt does not retract fully
the seat belt is hard to pull out
the seat belt gets hung

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle occupants may not receive the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash
despite meeting the deployment criteria
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries, distractions, or loss of control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without warning
often while the vehicle is in motion

and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to address airbag computer recall issues can lead to airbag failures, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Recalled airbag computer systems are not properly replaced or repaired
leaving the vehicle occupants at risk of airbag failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inconvenient airbag recall service can lead to delays or neglect of necessary repairs, putting vehicle occupants at risk.
symptoms: Dealerships or manufacturers fail to provide convenient and timely recall service
causing inconvenience to vehicle owners and potentially delaying necessary repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear and failure of rear brakes can cause reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and accidents.
symptoms: Rear brakes wear out quickly
replacement of rear brake components necessary.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pedal slippage can cause loss of control, accidents, or extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Noisy brakes and brake fade can cause reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and accidents.
